<http://www.example.org/meddevice#MedicalDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid3 .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#cardinality> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger> .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://www.example.org/meddevice#hasManufacturer> .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<http://www.example.org/meddevice#MedicalDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A device intended for medical use."@en .
<http://www.example.org/meddevice#MedicalDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Medical Device"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/meddevice#NearMissIncident
<http://www.example.org/meddevice#NearMissIncident> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/meddevice#NearMissIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/meddevice#Incident> .
<http://www.example.org/meddevice#NearMissIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Incident that could have caused harm but did not."@en .
<http://www.example.org/meddevice#NearMissIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Near-Miss Incident"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/meddevice#Recall
<http://www.example.org/meddevice#Recall> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
